      "content": "Empirical evidence from countries with universal systems consistently shows better population health outcomes, such as longer life expectancies and lower rates of preventable illness. Centralized planning is demonstrably superior at ensuring coverage for every citizen, eliminating the financial barriers that plague private insurance models. While efficiency concerns are often raised, the primary function of a healthcare system is to maintain public health, which centralized models are uniquely structured to guarantee.",
      "source": "target",
